Thania Dhoogra, from the N3 Toll Concession, speaks to #eNCA about this. Courtesy #DStv403 KWAZULU-NATAL - The N3 in KwaZulu-Natal is now open to traffic in both directions. The road was closed after protesters torched several trucks calling for the release of former president Jacob Zuma. The N3 Toll Concession's Thania Dhoogra says they appreciate the deployment of law enforcement officials. The N3 toll route has reopened after several trucks were burnt there. eNCA senior reporter Siphamandla Goge brings you the latest. Courtesy #DStv403 Some protesters have been arrested for public violence. WATCH | Zuma foundation defends KZN protest action Zuma is in jail as part of his 15-month sentence handed down by the Constitutional Court for contempt. Watch the video above for more details on this story.